questions_title: Questions? We have answers.
questions:
    - inquiry: What does Aptible do?
      response: |
        We help our customers with everything they need to build a modern HIPAA compliant web application. We not only handle the application core but also the compliance and administration. Additionally, we help our customers integrate with a wide variety of technical partners in HIPAA compliant ways.  
    - inquiry: Does my company need to be HIPAA compliant?
      response: |
        It’s possible! It’s not always easy to know whether or not you need to be HIPAA compliant, but if you answer “yes” to any of the below questions, then we should definitely talk:

        * Do you handle personally identifiable health information?
        * Do you need BAAs?  
        * Do you partner with or sell to hospitals or insurance companies?   

        Did you answer yes to any of these?  [Get in touch](/company/contact).
    - inquiry: How does Aptible’s technology work? What’s a container?
      response: >
        Aptible runs on AWS. We use Docker to build and run our customers’ applications and manage all DevOps while our customers have the power to manage their own code. These containers act as a lightweight virtual machine that can be used to run an instance of an application or a database. Our PHI-ready accounts each receive a virtual private cloud with secure software and servers that manage compliance. You can check out our [technology architecture here](/pages/assets/aptible-reference-architecture.pdf) and read more about [our technology here](/technology).
    - inquiry: What do I need to move from a Dev Account to a Platform or Production Account?
      response: |
        Easy!  You’ll need to sign 3 documents: Business Associate Agreement (BAA), mNDA, and Billing agreement.  It takes 15 seconds to execute these agreements, and we can have you back up and running in a few hours.  When you are ready to make the transition, [let us know](/company/contact).
    - inquiry: What else might I need to become HIPAA Compliant?
      response: |
        Depending on your specific business, you may need:

        * Independent 3rd party for Security Assessment
        * Logging and Analytics Providers who handle PHI 
        * Telephony, Email, Object storage 


